  "title": "Current Account",
  "description": "A bank account upon which the financial position of current account agreement is managed. \r\n\r\n\r\nComment: A current account is also called a check account. It is often classified as a non-interest bearing account, as often the deposits do not yield interest.\r\n\r\nPayment Services Directive (PSD) defines Current Account as a type of Payment Account. Payment Account means an account held in the name of one or more consumers that is used primarily for the execution of payment transactions. (PSD, 2007/64/EC)",
